A '''house dish''' is a very large wooden [[dishware|dish]], often ornately carved and painted in various human or animal figures, used in [[First Nations]] ceremonies in [[British Columbia]]. House dishes may be reserved only for special foodstuffs and not used for more common fare.

[[image:Lukwalil (house dish) beaver 2009.jpg|thumb|300px|A house dish in the shape of a beaver, in the [[Museum of Anthropology at UBC]].]]

