NWoC8C&pg=PA222&lpg=PA222 |title=Cléo de Mérode and the Rise of Modern Celebrity Culture |first=Michael D. |last=Garval |publisher=[[Ashgate Publishing]] |isbn=978-1-40940603-7 |year=2012 |page=222}}</ref><ref name=Merode2>{{cite web|first=Juan Arturo |last=Andrade Mendoza |title=Les Symboles Sexuels Anciens (2) : Clèo de Merode |url=http://my.opera.com:80/montcha670629/albums/show.dml?id=831856 |publisher=My Opera |date=23 July 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100401045751/http://my.opera.com/montcha670629/albums/show.dml?id=831856 |archivedate=1 April 2010 |accessdate=30 March 2017 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> * [[Alla Nazimova]]<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=YnkHAQAAIAAJ&q=%22lesbian+sex+symbol%22&dq=%22lesbian+sex+symbol%22 |title=Film |accessdate=30 December 2014|year=1977 }}</ref> * [[Ramon Novarro]]<ref name=FTU/><ref name="WVobit">Obituary ''Variety'', 6 November 1968, page 71.</ref> * [[Lillian Russell]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KtR81ZN533gC&pg=PA215 |title=Lillian Russell: A Biography of America's Beauty |first=Armond |last=Fields |publisher=[[McFarland & Company|McFarland]] |year=2008 |ISBN=978-0-7864-3868-6 |page=215}}</ref> * [[Gloria Swanson]]<ref name=FTU/> * [[Norma Talmadge]]<ref name=FTU/> * [[Rudolph Valentino]]<ref name=FTU/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.askmen.com/fashion/style_icon_100/134_style-icon-rudolph-valentino.html |work= Askmen |location=USA |title=Rudolph Valentino: Style Icon |date=22 October 2009 |accessdate=1 April 2011}}</ref><ref name="BizarreBytes"/>
